World Champion Shane Jamil Hill- Taylor wins lightweight gold at the Charlotte Open
Shane Jamil Hill-Taylor won gold in the lightweight division at the Charlotte Open, finishing his opponent in the final with this perfectly executed flying triangle!

Gold at Charlotte today. 
1 by points
1 by sub

It's been a long road to recovery. I've been away from BJJ for almost 6 whole months trying to get better. 

I decided a few weeks ago to start training and to come out to compete here in Charlotte. 

I'm still not back yet. This was just a personal test and honestly one of the dumbest things I've ever done in my life 😂. 

No training at my normal gym. No sleep. No coach. No neck (pause). No medical clearance to train/compete. No checking my weight before I came here... really dumb stuff but we made it happen💀😂

I had no business being here let alone competing and I'm paying for it now..but I had 2 fun matches against 2 new black belts who I've been watching and who's styles I really like so it was worth it. 

Thank you to everyone that has been supporting me on this journey back. 

I'll be back soon.. and I may be making some more dumb decisions soon so stay tuned😂🦾

Thank you everyone at @crazy88mma for the help in getting ready for this tournament 

S/o @karina_lagrana @shortroundbjj @drileyjj @dinhbjj @s.h.a.n.e_a for beating me up the past few weeks without hurting me. 

S/o to my @lloydirvinmma fam who's been reaching out and checking on me on my road to recovery. I'll see y'all soon. 

Also s/o to the medic guy at the venue who helped me be able to do my finals after I hurt myself in my first match...and s/o Celsius cola flavor. And s/o Flavios pizza for making me 2 pounds overweight
